 BY FOLASHADE KEHINDE THE West African Examinations Council, WAEC Nigeria, has confirmed January 29 as registration deadline for the West African Senior School Certificate Examination (WASSCE) for private candidates, 2021-First Series. Head, Public Affairs, WAEC, Demianus Ojijeogu, confirmed this. WAEC Zonal Office, Benin City, Edo State, had earlier put out a notice, saying, “The West African Examinations Council invites potential candidates to register for the West African Senior School Certificate Examination ( WASSCE)  for private candidates, 2021-First Series. “Registration pins and information CDs can be obtained at WAEC office, Aduwawa Benin city, banks and accredited agents. “Entry closes on January 29th, 2021. Registration fee is N3, 950, 00.” Ojijeogu confirmed that the public announcement was from its Zonal office in Benin, adding that “this information applies to Nigerians who want to sit for WASSCE this year. The pin can be gotten from any WAEC office nearest to them.”  